### Foster care payments

You can decide if you want to become licensed. As a licensed caregiver, you can get monthly foster care payments. You can get these while you’re caring for a child placed by DCYF, a Tribe, or other jurisdiction. 

These payments have lots of different names:

* Foster care maintenance payments (FCMPs)  
* Foster care reimbursements  
* Caregiver support resource level payments

Foster care payments reimburse you for the cost of: 

* Food  
* Clothing  
* Shelter  
* Other caregiving expenses

Payments are sent the following month. For example, if you have a child in your care in May, you’ll get payment for that care in June. Learn [how to get payments](./payments-how/). 

{% Callout %}Foster care maintenance payments are reimbursements and not income. You should not report them as income to the IRS. They should not affect your taxes but may affect your eligibility for benefits.{% endCallout %}

